FPUS53 KPAH 271900
ZFPPAH

Zone Forecast Product
National Weather Service Paducah KY
158 PM CDT Sun Jul 27 2025

KYZ005-272100-
McCracken-
Including the city of Paducah
158 PM CDT Sun Jul 27 2025

...HEAT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CDT /1 PM EDT/
MONDAY...
...EXTREME HEAT WARNING IN EFFECT FROM NOON MONDAY TO 8 PM CDT
TUESDAY...
...EXTREME HEAT WATCH IN EFFECT FROM TUESDAY EVENING THROUGH
WEDNESDAY EVENING...

.THIS AFTERNOON...Mostly sunny with a slight chance of showers
and thunderstorms. Highs in the lower 90s. Southwest winds 5 to
10 mph. Chance of rain 20 percent. Highest heat index readings
heat index readings up to 105.
.TONIGHT...Mostly clear. Humid with lows in the mid 70s.
Southwest winds around 5 mph in the evening, becoming light and
variable.
.MONDAY...Mostly sunny. A chance of showers and thunderstorms in
the afternoon. Humid with highs in the mid 90s. West winds around
5 mph. Chance of rain 30 percent. Highest heat index readings
heat index readings up to 112 in the afternoon.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy in the evening, then clearing.
Humid with lows in the upper 70s. Calm winds.
.TUESDAY...Sunny, hot with highs in the upper 90s. Calm winds.
Highest heat index readings heat index readings up to 110 in the
afternoon.
.TUESDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Lows in the upper 70s.
.WEDNESDAY...Sunny. A chance of showers and thunderstorms in the
afternoon. Hot with highs in the mid 90s. Chance of rain
40 percent. Highest heat index readings heat index readings up to
105 in the afternoon.
.WEDNESDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy with a chance of showers and
thunderstorms. Lows in the lower 70s. Chance of rain 50 percent.
.THURSDAY...Partly sunny. A chance of showers and thunderstorms
in the morning, then showers and thunderstorms likely in the
afternoon. Highs in the upper 80s. Chance of rain 70 percent.
.THURSDAY NIGHT...Mostly cloudy. A chance of showers and
thunderstorms in the evening. Lows in the upper 60s. Chance of
rain 50 percent.
.FRIDAY...Partly sunny. A chance of showers and thunderstorms in
the afternoon. Highs in the lower 80s. Chance of rain 30 percent.
.FRIDAY NIGHT AND SATURDAY...Partly cloudy. Lows in the mid 60s.
Highs in the lower 80s.

$$

INZ086-272100-
Vanderburgh-
Including the city of Evansville
158 PM CDT Sun Jul 27 2025

...HEAT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CDT /1 PM EDT/
MONDAY...
...EXTREME HEAT WARNING IN EFFECT FROM NOON MONDAY TO 8 PM CDT
TUESDAY...
...EXTREME HEAT WATCH IN EFFECT FROM TUESDAY EVENING THROUGH
WEDNESDAY EVENING...

.THIS AFTERNOON...Partly sunny with a chance of showers and
thunderstorms. Near steady temperature in the lower 90s.
Southwest winds around 10 mph. Chance of rain 30 percent. Highest
heat index readings heat index readings up to 106.
.TONIGHT...Partly cloudy. A slight chance of showers and
thunderstorms in the evening. Humid with lows in the mid 70s.
Southwest winds around 5 mph in the evening, becoming light and
variable. Chance of rain 20 percent.
.MONDAY...Mostly sunny. Humid with highs in the mid 90s.
Southwest winds around 5 mph. Highest heat index readings heat
index readings up to 110 in the afternoon.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy in the evening, then clearing.
Humid with lows in the upper 70s. West winds around 5 mph in the
evening, becoming light and variable.
.TUESDAY...Sunny, hot with highs in the mid 90s. Calm winds,
becoming north around 5 mph in the afternoon. Highest heat index
readings heat index readings up to 109 in the afternoon.
.TUESDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Lows in the upper 70s.
.WEDNESDAY...Mostly sunny. A chance of showers and thunderstorms
in the afternoon. Hot with highs in the mid 90s. Chance of rain
40 percent. Highest heat index readings heat index readings up to
105 in the afternoon.
.WEDNESDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy in the evening, then becoming
mostly cloudy. A chance of showers and thunderstorms. Lows in the
lower 70s. Chance of rain 50 percent.
.THURSDAY...Partly sunny. A chance of showers in the morning,
then showers likely with a chance of thunderstorms in the
afternoon. Highs in the mid 80s. Chance of rain 60 percent.
.THURSDAY NIGHT...Mostly cloudy with a chance of showers in the
evening, then partly cloudy after midnight. Lows in the upper
60s. Chance of rain 30 percent.
.FRIDAY...Mostly sunny. Highs in the lower 80s.
.FRIDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Lows in the lower 60s.
.SATURDAY...Mostly sunny. Highs in the lower 80s.

$$

KYZ019-272100-
Daviess-
Including the city of Owensboro
158 PM CDT Sun Jul 27 2025

...HEAT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CDT /1 PM EDT/
MONDAY...
...EXTREME HEAT WARNING IN EFFECT FROM NOON MONDAY TO 8 PM CDT
TUESDAY...
...EXTREME HEAT WATCH IN EFFECT FROM TUESDAY EVENING THROUGH
WEDNESDAY EVENING...

.THIS AFTERNOON...Partly sunny with a chance of showers and
thunderstorms. Near steady temperature around 90. Southwest winds
5 to 10 mph. Chance of rain 40 percent.
.TONIGHT...Partly cloudy. A slight chance of showers and
thunderstorms in the evening. Humid with lows in the mid 70s.
Southwest winds around 5 mph. Chance of rain 20 percent.
.MONDAY...Mostly sunny. Humid with highs in the lower 90s.
Southwest winds around 5 mph. Highest heat index readings heat
index readings up to 109 in the afternoon.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy. Humid with lows in the mid 70s.
West winds around 5 mph in the evening, becoming light and
variable.
.TUESDAY...Mostly sunny. Hot with highs in the mid 90s. Calm
winds, becoming northeast around 5 mph in the afternoon. Highest
heat index readings heat index readings up to 109 in the
afternoon.
.TUESDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Lows in the upper 70s.
.WEDNESDAY...Mostly sunny. A chance of showers and thunderstorms
in the afternoon. Highs in the mid 90s. Chance of rain
